  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Assistance in Shelter and Support to the Site Management for Vulnerable Populations Affected by Conflicts in Ituri and North Kivu, Democratic Republic of the Congo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The intervention aims to improve the living conditions of conflict-affected populations residing in displacement sites and host communities in the Democratic Republic of the Congo. Through this project, IOM is providing shelter (rehabilitation and construction of transitional shelters) and camp coordination and camp management assistance to internally displaced persons and returnees (including people with disabilities) in Ituri and North Kivu provinces.</narrative>
  </description>
